  "texts": [
    "These are mainly emotions but include some expressions like \"grrrr\".",
    "We use this dataset for our experiments.",
    "Figure 2 shows the aggregated frequencies of the 25 most commonly predicted emotions for all models per gender.",
    "We find stark gender differences: models attribute SADNESS to women 10,635 times and only 6,886 times to men; JOY is attributed 4,415 times and 6,520 times to men and women, respectively.",
    "In turn, ANGER is attributed to men almost twice as often as for women (13,173 times compared to 7,042)."
  ],
